column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Partly sunny- water temp. 62- 7-15 mph winds- ice out 4/26/93- crappies hitting.
Sunny- water temp 52- windy/gusts- ice out 4/26/93- adult eagles feeding eaglets.
Partly sunny- water temp 67- light gusts- lily pads 50% up.  Lake level: Rising
Partly sunny- light breeze- water temp 64.  Lake level: Rising
Overcast- water temp 67- weed cover- 1 baby loon missing
Sunny- blue sky- water temp is 72 degrees.  Lake inlet is totally blocked by a beaver dam!  Outlet is still flowing.  Beaver dams are downstream also.
Sunny- summer conditions.  Water temp is 72 degrees.  Eaglet has left his nest.  Lake level: steady
Sunny- gentle breeze- water temp is 68 degrees- weeds are declining.  Blue herons are gone.  100+ grackles flew through.
Sunny- windy- water temp is 50 degrees- weeds are 75% gone.  Bald eagle and baby on the lake.  Lake level: Rising
Cloudy- winds are calm.  1/4" of ice on 80% of the lake.  Water temp is 36 degrees.  Lake level: steady
Loons back- sunny/hazy/winds 5 mph- water temp. 46 degrees- ice-off 4/15/94- muskrats active.
Bright sunshine/light winds.  Water temp. 52 degrees- bald eagle has hatched- loon has gone on the nest.
Good weather- water temp. 72 degrees- swimming- bull rushes all up.  Loon still on nest.
Warm-humid weather in the 90's- swimming good.  Loons have 2 babies- water temp. 74 degrees.
Stirred up by motors.  Weeds up 100% .  Lots of boating activity.  Warm + humid.
Lots of algae on weeds.  Eaglet has left his nest.  Night hawks are back.
Weeds bent over below water level.  Water temp. 65 degrees.
Floating algae balls weeds under water.  8" of rain through 9/26/94.
Water temp. 52 degrees F.  Loons have left.  Boat traffic is way down.  Warm-mild fall.  90% of leaves are down.
Water temp. 44 degrees F- ice out 4/15/95.  Loons have returned.  Eagles are on the nest.
Water temp. 62 degrees F/air 82 degrees F- wind 5-10 mph/bull rushes 50% above water/water lilies floating.
Water temp. 82 degrees/air temp 99 degrees F.  No wind- weed growth 90% complete.  2 eaglets in nest.  Loon just went on her nest.
Water temp. 70 degrees- weed growth 100%.  Loon has abandoned her nest.  Two eggs in nest.
Sunny- 15 mph wind- sediment accumulation on windward shore/foam 74 degrees air temp.  Water level: up 4"
Water temp. 68 degrees.  Overcast- some weeds are brown and fallen over.
Sunny- 82 degrees air temp.  Boat traffic down.  Weeds heavy.  Lake level: Rising
Water temp. 64 degrees- air temp. 50 degrees- wind 25 mph gusts.  Sunny.
Sunny- 59 degrees air temp.- 62 degrees water temp.  Two adult eagles back at nest eaglets gone.
Cloudy- 52 degree air- 52 degrees water.  Windy- weeds 80% gone.
Cloudy- rain- 52 degree air- 50 degree water- loons gone-migrating- diving ducks here.
Sedimentary matter.  Ice out May 18- 1996.  Tow baby eagles hatched 5-1-96.  5 adult loons on lake.  Water temperature 44 degrees.
Water temperature is 64 degrees- water lily leaves showing- reeds bearly showing- cloudy day.  Need rain.  Loons did not nest yet.  Man made loon nest on the lake.
Public perception due to pollen.  Water temp. 70 degrees.  Baby ducks showing bulrushes up.  Heavy pollen on lake surface.  Partly cloudy day.
Water temp. 72 degrees.  Sunny- pollen has cleared.  Weed growth full blown.  Lost use of lake due to 2 jet skis on lake for 8 hours.
Water temp. 69 degrees.  Fishing off due to pressure changes.  Lots of duck family on lake. 5 adult loons on lake.
Water temperature is 68 degrees.  Both eagles have left the nest.  Fishing fair- weeds are heavy.
Water temp. 72 degrees- water level high due to 3 beaver dams on our outlet.  Weed spread is larger than other years.  Sunny + 82 degrees air temp.
Sunny- air temp. 80 degrees.  Water temp. 72 degrees. 3 beaver dams removed downstream.  Lake level dropped a foot.
Water temp. 52 degrees- weed level 50% down. Sunny. Clarity poor.
Water temp. 48 degrees.  Air temp. 72 degrees.  Sunny- warm.  Ducks around weeds 50% gone.  Loons gone.
Water temperature 34 degrees- ice out 4/24/97.  Pair of loons back- pair of eagles feeding 97 hatch.  Beavers are active at 8 pm.
Water temperature 56 degrees- 3 beaver dams downstream.  High water so island is submerged.  No loon nesting site- some fish action.
Bull rushes coming on.  Water lilies showing.  Loon is on her nest- muskrats active.  Water temperature 68 degrees. fishing is two weeks behind.
Water temperature is 72 degrees- loons have one baby.  Weeds up 75 percent.  Water murky with sedimentation.
Water temperature 70 degrees- air temperature 63 degrees.  Sediment particles are gone. 2 baby eagle very active.  Watercraft travel is heavy.
Water temperature 73 degrees.  Full weed bloom.  Pulled beaver dam downstream 4 weeks ago.  Lake level dropped 1 foot.  Lake is now rising.  Two eaglets now flying.
Water temperature 66 degrees.  Skiers have departed for 97.  Have baby loon- and two eaglets survived.  Lots of underwater weeds.  Not as many water lilies.
Water temperature 55 degrees.  Weeds all bent over.  Lots of ducks.  Peak color.  Water clarity very murky.
Water temperature 49 degrees.  Weeds 50% gone.  Yearling loon all alone.  No parents around.
Water temperature 36 degrees.  Weeds 90% gone.  No ducks- 1 eaglet and one adult here.
Water temp. 55 degrees.  Ice out 4/6/98.  Eagle on new nest.  Loons back muskrats out and about.
78 degrees. Water temp. 62 degrees. Thunderstorm watch.  Wind gusts.  Fishing good eaglets have hatched.
Wind at 20 mph water temp. 56 degrees.  No loons on the nest.
Calm.  Water temp. 76 degrees.  Weed growth on low side.  No baby ducks.
Water ski and jet ski boat traffic.  Water temp. 74 degrees.  Bottom sediment stirred up affecting clarity.
Water temp. 72 degrees.  Boat traffic normal.  One baby loon.  Eaglets eager to leave nest.  Full weed growth.
Water temp. 72 degrees.  Water skiing all day.  Bottom silt stirred up by 90 h.p.  3 eaglets in the nest 2 left in nest today.  One remains in the nest.
Air 80 degrees.  Water temp. 74 degrees.  No skiers. weeds starting to decline.  Baby loon almost adult size.  Baby eaglets still around.
Air 55 degrees.  Water temp. 50 degrees.  Baby loon all alone no adults.  No eaglets around.  Adult eagles here.  No muskrats.
Cloudy air 69 degrees.  Water temp. 48 degrees.  Baby loon gone.  Adult eagle around.  Weeds 80% gone.
Air 39 degrees water 34 degrees.  Lake froze 11/13/98.  End of season.
Beavers are active every night.  Mallards are back.  Pair of loons are on the lake.  Adult eagle is on her nest.  Air temp 69 F.  Water 48 F.
Water level dropping.  Eagles are feeding a newborn. winds out of the east.  No rain for last 4 weeks.  Air temp 75 F.  Water temp 60 F.
Adult loon on a manmade floating log nest in a protected bay.  Windy and warm.  Lots of rain.  Beaver dams on inlet + outlet.  Water 63 F.
Air temp 72 F.  Duck with 6 young.  Good rains in last two weeks.  Fine pollen very heavy on lake.  Pencil weeds full stock.  Water 60 F.
No baby loons.  No baby eagles.  Both pair unsuccessful. continuous cold and warm spells in June. 33 F for a night low.  Fishing is no good.  Water 65 F.
Two jet-skis on lake for 1 day.  Boat traffic at peak.  Air temp 75 F.  Fishing is way-off.  Deer flies heavy.  Water 69 F.
Daily water skiing so lake is murky. cut weeds.  Air temp 87 F.  Floating sediment.  A few duck families.  Water 78 F.
Vilas County hit by straight line winds (67 mph). 50-000 trees down.  No power for 4 days.  Lightning strikes. property damage.  Air temp 75 F.  Water 72 F.
Partly cloudy.  No boating.  Fishing is way-off.  Air temp 68 F.  Beavers have repaired their dams- both inlet + outlet.
Water temp 72 F. Air temp 88 F. Fishing has improved. Skiers have departed.  Very few boats on water. some turn-over on lake.
Water temp 55 F.  Air temp 59 F.  Fishing much improved.  52 1/2" musky caught and released.  Mallards scarce.  Eagle around.  Loons on the lake.
Water temp 47 F.  Air temp 59 F.  Wind gusts 30 mph.  Water turbid.  Weed growth 75% gone.  Leaves 75% down.  Otter around + eagle.
Water temp 38 F.  Air temp 52 F.  Ice forms along shoreline.  Skin of ice all over.  No wind.   Loons left 10-15.  Fishing poor.  End of season.
Water temperature is 42 degrees- loons arrived 3/31- ice out on 3/25- mallards are back- adult eagle went on the nest 3/6- and four beavers trapped down stream.
Water temperature is 44 degrees- muskrats out- adult eagles feeding a hatchling or hatchings in the nest- hatch occurred around April 12th- and had 1" of ice and snow.
Water temperature is 59 degrees- loons around investigating a floating man-made nest- eaglet has a 1" wing span- air temperature is 63 degrees- water level low- and weeds appearing.
Water temperature is 60 degrees- air temperature is 59 degrees- two eaglets in the nest- very active- adults feeding fish regularly- lots of cold fronts coming in- and still drought conditions.
Water temperature is 69 degrees- air temperature is 74 degrees- one baby loon two weeks old- 90% weed growth- many fronts passing through- and 4" of rain in 18 hours.
Water temperature is 74 degrees- air temperature is 79 degrees- 100% weed growth- skiers are active- fishing has improved with warmer water- and less total surface weeds.
Water temperature is 72 degrees- air temperature is 74 degrees- weed explosion- profusion of water bugs- both eaglets have fledged- baby loon alone diving- and daily water skiing.
Water temperature is 74 degrees- air temperature is 76 degrees- pontoon plane nc17up landed on Kathan Lake and took water samples- adult river otter and baby went by- and daily water skiing.
Water temperature is 67 degrees- air temperature is 66 degrees- lake quiet- no skiing- weeds dying slowly- mostly easterly winds- night hawks are passing through- and lake swallows are gone.
Water temperature is 58 degrees- air temperature is 70 degrees- hummingbirds gone- pencil weeds brown- and baby loon is airborne.
Water temperature is 47 degrees- air temperature is 54 degrees- no duck activity- fish have gone into dormant stages- and underwater weeds are still hardy.
Water temperature is 50 degrees- air temperature is 45 degrees- muskrat and adult eagle around as are two immature eagles.  End of season!
Water temperature is 59 degrees- air temperature is 70 degrees- ice out on 4/19/01- loons return on 4/20/01- eagle on the nest- and no fish to kill.
Water temperature is 62 degrees- air temperature is 82 degrees reed weeds are above water- water lilies are showing- loons not on the nest- and crappies are spawning.
Water temperature is 76 degrees- air temperature is 84 degrees- water reeds full grown- loons is nesting on the artificial floating nest- eagles have abandoned their nest and not successful.
Water temperature is 69 degrees- air temperature is 68 degrees- loons were not successful on incubation- and fishing is off due to Canadian cold fronts that come in each day.
Water temperature is 79 degrees- air temperature is 84 degrees- crappies are back as are boats- tuber- skiers- jet skis- and heavy wakes up to the shoreline- and fishing is good after 8 p.m..
Water temperature is 84 degrees- air temperature is 92 degrees- boating and jet ski activity on daily basis- floating gut weeds and high level of sedimentation present.
Water temperature is 67 degrees- air temperature is 72 degrees- boating and skiing has almost stopped- water clarity settling down- lots of snails present- and need rain.
Water temperature is 71 degrees- air temperature is 79 degrees- weeds are below the water level- reeds have their fall leather brown color- and ducks are scarce this year.
Water temperature is 59 degrees- air temperature is 68 degrees- terns are migrating- tree colors much delayed this year- loons are still here- humming birds are gone- and some birds are flocking.
Water temperature is 49 degrees- air temperature is 62 degrees- color at peak- don't see any muskrats but reeds are eaten down- and fishing improved with colder water.
Water temperature is 42 degrees- air temperature is 64- loons are gone- no ducks around- 7" of snow on trees and ground on October 26th- 2001- fast melt-down and skim of lake ice.
Water temp 49 F.  Air temp 42 F.  Ice out 4/17.  Loons return 4/18/02.  Eagles are feeding their brod.  Saw a muskrat.  One beaver roadkill. Pelt was salvaged.
Water temp 72 F.  Air temp 72 F.  Lots of pollen on water surface.  Eagles have 1 baby as do the loons - born 6/10/02.  Mallards around.  Turtles out.
Water temp 80 F.  Air temp 87 F.  1 family of ducks.  Mother and six goslings .  Swimming is good.  Skiers are out daily.  150 hp stirs up bottom sediment.
Water temp 81 F.  Air temp 82 F.  Baby loon is diving for food.  Baby eaglet has left the nest but still hanging around.
Water temp 72 F.  Air temp 65 F.  Skiing - tubing on a daily basis.  Weed growth heavy.  Fishing is hard now.  Rains have been consistent and heavy.
Water temp 68 F.  Air temp 68 F.  30-40 mph winds.  Fishing has improved.  Loons are flocking - six at a time.  Saw one muskrat.  Black bear (200 pound) visits.
Water temp 69 F.  Air temp 59 F.  Tornado watch.  Lots of rain.  Sun is now out and storm moving east.  Skiing has stopped.
Water temp 69 F.  Air temp 76 F.  Baby loon trying to take off but didn't make it.  Canadian geese dropped in.  Mallards are around.
Water temp 55 F.  Air temp 61 F.  Tree colors are at their peak.  Beaver on stream with a 20 ft dam- thus high water.

Water temp 39 F.  Air temp 49 F.  Both adult eagles back at their enxt.  Doing repair work.  1/2" of ice formed.  11/5/02 boats ran through the ice breaking it up into a million pieces.  End of season.
Water temp 42 F.  Air temp 63 F.  Ice out 4/16.  Loons on the lake.  Eagles are feeding something in their nest.  2 beavers are swimming.  No fish kill.
Water temp 58 F.  Air temp 60 F.  Six beavers trapped in Kathan prior to 4/30/03.  Loons not on nest yet.  Pan fish spawning in the shallows.  No crappies yet.
Water temp 68 F.  Air temp 70 F.  Female loon on artificial floating nest.  A pair of Canadian geese are in residence on lake.  Catch and release 37" northern.
Water temp 72 F.  Air temp 82 F.  Baby eagle big as a chicken.  Pair of loons have a new baby chick.  Duck families are not in sight.  Weeds full bloom.
Water temp 78 F.  Air temp 85 F.  Baby eagle out of nest on a limb.  Baby loon is now diving for food.  Sighted family of ducks 8 in number.  Boat traffic way up.
Water temp 73 F.  Air temp 77 F.  Eaglet has flown the coop.  Left the nest.  He returns to nest occasionally.  Very cold nights.  42 F for a low.
Water temp 73 F.  Air temp 79 F.  Daily tubing and skiing.  Weeds are full strength in growth.  Fishing fair.  Bass and crappies.
Water temp 78 F.  Air temp 86 F.  Baby loon diving on its own.  Adult loons still feed baby.  Beavers are back downstream with a 50 wide dam.
Water temp 65 F.  Air temp 83 F.  Clarity of water has improved as all water skiers have departed.  Maximum of 40 hp motor now in use.
Water temp 60 F.  Air temp 59 F. Weeds are dying back.  Loons and waterfowl are scarce.  Fishing is improving.  Northerns and bass.
Water temp 39 F.  Air temp 30 F.  Two inches of snow today.  Beaver dams downstream with water rising.  Open water will freeze any day.  Final report.
Water Temp 61F Air Temp. 50F Ice out 4/17/04- Loons back same day. Pair of Eagles are feeding and eaglet- fish like the warm water.
water temp 68F Air temp 72F fish just now spawning- crappies-bluegills- no boat traffic- one jet ski out
water temp 72F- air temp 77F- night lows of 43F- water level low- lack of rainfall during July. Eaglet did not survive this season. Loon had no hatch.
Water Temp 72F- Air Temp 74F- Lack of rain for 30 days- water level low- saw two families of ducks feeding in weeds- week-end lake use heavy- one jet ski.
Water Temp. 65F- Air Temp 75F- Eurasian milfoil reported in Kathan Lake. Lots of cold fronts in and out making fishing impossible. 36-40F nightly lows.
water temp.  72F- air temp. 78F- very quiet Labor Day Activity-thus high clarity. Duck Population seems down. Loons are active Daily. Stump Muchrooms all over.
water temp. 61F Sept. Exceptionally warm -80F everyday
water temp. 51F- Oct. Very warm. Fishing-way off of normal. Pier out for the winter.
Water temp. 50 F- air temp. 68 F.  Ice out 4/11/2005.  Pair of loons are active.  Pair of eagles are in their old nest tending to an eaglet or more.  First boat on the lake.
Air temp. 58 F.  Water temp. 58 F.Muskrats are active.  Fishing is slow due to cold water temps.  Pan fish are coming in to spawn in weed beds.
Water temp. 68 F.  Air temp. 77 F.  Loon is on her nest.  Eagles have two eaglets.  Feeding them can be a lot of work.  Adult eagles are taking baby ducks.
Water temp. 78 F.  Air temp. 75 F.  Weed growth at its prime.  Water skiiers are out today.  Loons have one baby.  Two eaglets are over 16 " tall.
Water temp. 80 F.  Air temp. 69 F.  Both eaglets have left the nest but return now and then.  Adults keep their distance.  Baby loon is 15 " long.
Water temp. 78 F.  Air temp. 90 F.  Eurasian water milfoil has a good start in one bay and shows in 2-3 other bays.  Fishing is way off with high water temps.  Eaglets all over.
Water temp. 72 F- air temp. 73 F.  Skiing activity has diminished with school starting.  Kathan Lake Association is now registered with the state.  Milfoil eradication next.
Water temp. 66 F.  Air temp. 70 F.  Loons come in to visit.  Kayaks- motor boats- row boats- knee-boarders- skiers all activ on Labor Day.  Observed a Canada goose.
Water temp. 68 F.  Air temp. 78 F.  100 +/- Canada geese landed for a stop over.  Some rainfall- but need 6" to make a difference in water level.
Water temp. 61 F.  Air temp. 74 F.  Baby loon has been left alone by the parents trying to get him to fly by Oct. 15.  He or she is adult in size and ready to depart.
Water temp 34 F- air temp 50 F.  Ice out 4/12.  Eagle is on their old nest.  April has set a record for warm temperatures.  Very dry.  No rain.
Water temp 50 F.  Air temp 62 F.  Eagles have something in their nest.  Loons are back - 1 pair on Kathan Lake.  Mallards are active.
Water temp 59 F- air temp 48 F.  Eagles are feeding 2 eaglets.  Had a mother black bear with 4 cubs visit our deck for feed.  This is the third visit.
Water temp 72 F- air temp 76 F.  There are two eaglets.  Not many duck babies yet.
Water temp 68 F- air temp 72 F.  Pair of loons with one baby loon appear 6/14/2006.  Baby eaglets are spreading their wings for exercise.  Lack of rain.
Water temp 80 F.  Air temp 90 F.  Both eaglets left the nest 7/7/2006.  The adults are nowhere in view.  Weeds in full bloom.  Drought conditions.
Water temp 66 F.  Air temp 77 F.  6" of new rain in the last ten days.  Baby loon is making good progress.  Three or four ski boats weekly.  Swimming is great.
Water temp 70 F.  Air temp 79 F.  Milfoil clusters are scattered throughout the lake.  Good weeds are more prominent this season.  Fishing is off.
Water temp 72 F.  Air temp 74 F.  Water traffic busy Labor Day.  Lake is now quiet.  Loons are able to use 100% of the lake again.  Baby eagle trying his luck at diving but no success.
Water temp 58 F.  Air temp 50 F.  Seasonal owners have departed.  Lake is quiet.  Baby loon is all alone.  Has thirty days to fly.  Colors on trees is about 50% of peak.

column1: Both adult eagles are present- sitting on large rocks waiting for a tasty northern

column2: Water temp. 55 F.  Air temp 62 F.  Onterra lake consultant has identified 82 acres of milfoil in Kathan Lake.  Treatment is not financially possible in 2009.  Eagles and loons are active.
Water temp 59 F.  Air temp 52 F.  Canadian cold fronts continue.  2 eagles are active.  Loon on the nest.  Milfoil is 3-4 feet tall in infested areas.
Water temp 69 F.  Air temp 75 F.  Lake water covered with pollen.  2 baby loons are being fed.  Tubing and skiing has started.  Milfoil growth restricts boating and fishing.
Property owners have decided NOT to put their boats and pontoons in the water due to milfoil hazard.
Water temp 70 F.  Air temp 73 F.  Lack of activity on lake due to plentiful milfoil.
Lost 1 baby loon- calling for food but no adults around.  2 eaglets are still in the lake area.
Water temp 63 F.  Air temp 69 F.  Fishing results are off due to cold fronts and milfoil restrictions.  Saw 1 beaver dam downstream.
Water temp 51 F.  Air temp 59 F.  Much needed rain 3"-4".  Hummingbirds are gone.  1 baby loon on the water.

column1: Ice out 3/26 No snow in March
Eagles are feeding an eaglet or to
Lake to be treated with 2-4-D May 12-113 acres
Lake was treated by professionals with liquid 2-4-D May 13th. No visible fish kill
Very Minor Boat due to warnings of water hazard
Lots of boat traffic for 4th of July
Lost two baby loons to pradators - 1 week old.
Boat traffic down - no clams or mussels around

column2: Water high and clarity low. Many weeds floating and dead snails. Lot of silt floating in the water my assumption this is because of the recent milfoil treatment which killed back a lot of milfoil which once held the silt in place. Silt is so bad that when swiming you can clearly see a brown hue of silt on your body when leaving water.

column1: Baby eagles still around- 1 adult loon around
Two river otters eating of the pier

column2: Lake water is brown and murky silty looking
Calm- warm and cloudy cloudy- light wind- some boat traffic
partly cloudy- cool- light wind- some boat traffic
sunny- windy- hot and humid- no boat traffic
Sunny and breezy. No boats on lake.
Sunny and calm. No boats on the lake.
Sunny and breezy. No boats. sunny and breezy. No boats.
sunny and calm. sunny and calm.
